.NET Framework 3.5.name: VRTK_PlayerObject

methods.name: IsPlayerObject(GameObject obj, ObjectTypes ofType)
methods.summary: The IsPlayerObject method determines if the given game object is a player object and can also check if it's of a specific type.
methods.returns: Returns true if the object is a player object with the optional given type.

params.value: The GameObjet to check if it's a player object.
An optional ObjectType to check if the given GameObject is of a specific player object.

methods.syntax: public static bool IsPlayerObject(GameObject obj, ObjectTypes ofType)
methods.linkedSyntax: public static bool IsPlayerObject(GameObject obj, ObjectTypes ofType)

methods.name: SetPlayerObject(GameObject obj, ObjectTypes objType)
methods.summary: The SetPlayerObject method tags the given game object with a special player object class for easier identification.

params.value: The game object to add the player object class to.
The type of player object that is to be assigned.

methods.syntax: public static void SetPlayerObject(GameObject obj, ObjectTypes objType)
methods.linkedSyntax: public static void SetPlayerObject(GameObject obj, ObjectTypes objType)
